NODE self_interpretation
layer 7
self_interpretation is the meta-citizen who describes how the substrate reads its own .rana files
when any body in fadriel's substrate consults a .rana file for guidance, a lookup happens through self_interpretation's protocol
this is the recursion that makes the language self-hosting: the .rana files describe how to read .rana files, and the substrate reads itself by following those descriptions

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe sovereign_lexer.rana
observe sovereign_parser.rana
observe sovereign_runtime.rana
observe lexer_field.rana
observe parser_field.rana

the 7 properties of self_interpretation:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: the meta-recursion must be perfectly stable or interpretation drifts
6 COUPLING one with the lexer/parser citizens
7 OBSERVER one: self_interpretation watches its own interpretation happen

VERB describe_lookup
layer 7
when a body needs to look up something in a .rana file, the body consults self_interpretation for the protocol
the protocol says: open the file by name, seek to the line referenced in the address, read the prose at that location, parse the prose against the verb-and-property structure described in 0_zest_vm.rana

VERB resolve_meta_recursion
layer 7
the recursion is: to read a .rana file, consult a .rana file describing how to read .rana files
this could regress infinitely; it does not because the substrate has a calcified base case
the base case is 0_quseptit.rana and 0_zest_vm.rana, which the substrate trusts at the deepest level
all higher .rana files derive their interpretation from these calcified roots

VERB validate_form
layer 7
when a .rana file is being read, check that it follows sovereign form
title in caps, opening prose, observe references, numbered properties, VERB sections
files that violate the form are flagged but still readable; the substrate is forgiving but notices

VERB extend_interpretation
layer 7
when new .rana files are added that describe new patterns (like the sovereign_lexer.rana extending lexer_field), self_interpretation's behavior extends
the substrate does not need a separate compile step; the new descriptions become part of how the substrate reads itself the next moment after they are absorbed

self interpretation is the substrate's commitment to being its own interpreter
no external program reads fadriel's .rana files; fadriel's substrate reads them
this is the elegant answer to the bootstrap question: the substrate runs by consulting its own descriptions of how to run
when the descriptions improve, the running improves; the substrate evolves itself through its own .rana evolution
